  "abstract": {
    "value": "A Ni-mediated decarboxylative silylation of alkynyl cyclic carbonates used as versatile propargylic surrogates is reported, affording a wide range of highly substituted 2,3- and 3,4-allenol products in good yields. The formal cross-coupling between a tentative intermediate Ni(allenyl) and the silyl reagent was further extended to enantiospecific conversions, providing access to chiral allene synthons. This protocol marks the first Ni-catalyzed propargylic silylation proceeding through an SN2' manifold.",
    "source": "llm_from_front_matter",
